http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/Dalits%E2%80%99-expulsion/article13993374.ece

In the wee hours of Sunday over 50 students of University of Hyderabad slept in an open ground to protest expulsion of five Dalit research scholars from the varsity’s hostel.The scholars have been sleeping out in the open at the varsity’s shopping complex ground for eight consecutive days after they got expelled demanding UoH to roll back the expulsion.The research scholars protest is backed by 10 student outfits on campus. The five were expelled as per the results of a probe done by the varsity into a scuffle between two student outfits, ASA and Akhil Bharatiya Vidyarthi Parishad (ABVP). Over fifty student supporters, who had gathered at shopping complex on Saturday night, sang songs, shouted slogans and finally went to sleep after 12 a.m.